description: Unknown. Possibly adopted from German hurra, itself of uncertain origin, or possibly an alteration of huzzah.

entries.meaning: A cheer; a cry of hurrah!.

verbs.description: hurrah (third-person singular simple present hurrahs, present participle hurrahing, simple past and past participle hurrahed)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To give a hurrah (to somebody).
